13 Sec. 3. 28 V.S.A. § 709 is added to read:
14 § 709. OUT-OF-STATE FACILITIES; PROHIBITIONS
15 (a) Facility prohibitions.
16 (1) No individual under the custody of the Commissioner shall be
17 supervised, housed, treated, or cared for in an out-of-state correctional facility
18 unless it is operated by a public or nonprofit entity to house individuals
19 pursuant to an interstate compact or federal contract.
20 (2) The Department shall not employ any rehabilitative, educational,
21 health care, or other support services provided by a private or for-profit entity.
